  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nSPX is sitting right at the max positive gamma strike of 6850, putting dealers in aggressive selling mode as they hedge long gamma positions - the recent 4.1% 1-minute move triggered a \"wall_break\" event as price pushed through this critical level. With spot now above the GEX flip at 6837 in a PIN regime, dealers are likely dumping delta into this strength, creating natural resistance around the 6850-6875 gamma wall cluster. Watch for mean reversion back toward 6837 as the massive +9.2B gamma wall at 6850 should act as a magnet, while any push toward 6900 faces another substantial +6.8B wall where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back down toward 6850 as dealers sell the rally.",
